$ /etc/passwd

→ Linux/user[User] account information: each line represents a user and is colon-seperated with the following fields:

1) username,
-
2) → development/security/password[password] [nowadays usually x, see → Linux/fhs/etc/shadow ]
-
3) user id
-
4) default → Linux/group[group] id [See → Linux/fhs/etc/group]
-
5) gecos,
-
6) The user's → Linux/home-directory,
-
7) The name of the program to be run when a user logs in, usually a → Linux/shell/index.

In order to prohibit a user from logging in, the programm to be launched (7) might be set to `/bin/false`

The file should be edited with → Linux/shell/commands/vipw[`vipw`].

sa:
  → Linux/fhs/etc/group

  → Linux/shell/commands/getent[`getent`]

  → Linux/shell/commands[Shell commands] → Linux/shell/commands/chpasswd[`chpasswd`] and → Linux/shell/commands/passwd[`passwd`]

  → Linux/security/password
